The paper focuses on analyzing facial behavior using deep generative models and convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with analyzing multimedia data featuring sparse examples of signals of interest, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses audience engagement and disengagement, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
